I go to Chipotle often and to many locations. This is the only location that I have had consistent bad service. The often uncaring attitude from some, but not all, the employees is a turn off. Every visit to this store has at least one employee not following mask guidelines. Today however was worse. Upon walking into the store one of the employees was eating at the chair closest to and facing the entrance and exit. I know you have to take your mask off to eat, but with the many places and directions to sit the employee chose the one that puts others at risk. Then the employee helping put together my meal did not have her mask on right either. Lastly, this location barely cooks their veggies and has been the only one to refuse to get me extra cilantro, and multiple times. These last couple things, while annoying, I can deal with, but not the ignoring the mask policy.. This location needs an intervention from corporate.

I placed an online order for a group meeting at the office. The delivery arrived on time (they use Door Dash for delivery). However, the Door Dash driver only picked up part of the order. When I called Chipotle, the young lady let me know, she had been trying to contact the driver, but he didn't answer his phone.  She apologized for what happened and asked how far was my office from their location, I told her about 4 blocks. She said, "Ok, someone will be delivering your order shortly." Within 10 minutes a young lady walked into our building with the order! Customer service at its best!!
